# Documentation Rewrite Directive — Classroom Token Hub

> **Audience:** An autonomous AI agent with no prior knowledge of this project.
> **Objective:** Produce a coherent, predictable, deduplicated, and structurally sound documentation system under `/docs` with a single source of truth for every topic.
>
> **Exclusion:** `docs/user-guides/` and `docs/GITHUB_SITE/` are **out of scope** for this project. Do not move, rename, rewrite, or restructure any file within those directories. User-guides will be a separate future project.

---

## 1. Project Context

Classroom Token Hub is a Flask web application that models a classroom economy. Students earn wages via attendance, spend at a store, pay rent, purchase insurance, and manage savings. Teachers configure all economic parameters per-class. System admins have oversight across teachers.

Key architectural concept: **`join_code`** is the isolation boundary. Every financial operation, query, and data scope is anchored to a `join_code`. This is the most important invariant in the system.

The application has three user roles: **Student**, **Teacher (Admin)**, and **System Admin** — each with separate dashboards, routes, and permissions.

