## 2. Documentation Hierarchy (Preserve Exactly)

The project uses a formal authority hierarchy defined in `INV-CORE-001_Authority_Model.md`. This hierarchy MUST be preserved:

```
Tier 0 — Foundational (INV-CORE-000, INV-CORE-001, SOP-DOC-000)
  ↓
Tier 1 — Constitutional (ARC-*, DOM-*, SEC-Architecture)
  ↓
Tier 2 — Normative (FEAT-*, SOP-*, .claude/rules/*)
  ↓
Tier 3 — Informative (LOG-*, SEC-Records, user-guides, root files)
```

Six formal **Divisions** exist, defined in `SOP-DOC-003_Division_Definition.md`:

| Division | Code | Tier | Purpose |
|---|---|---|---|
| ARCHITECTURE | ARC | Constitutional | Cross-domain system design, identity, authorization, ledger |
| DOMAINS | DOM | Constitutional | Bounded business contexts (Rent, Bank, Pay, Insurance, Store) |
| FEATURES | FEAT | Normative | User-facing workflows and implementations of domain capability |
| STANDARD OPERATING PROCEDURES | SOP | Normative | Human procedures: deployment, migration, documentation governance |
| SECURITY | SEC | Mixed | Constitutional (threat models, controls) + Informative (audit reports, incidents) |
| LOGS | LOG | Informative | Historical records, release notes, milestones, postmortems |

Plus two non-namespace locations:
- `docs/user-guides/` — Informative, user-facing instructional content
- Root files (`README.md`, `CHANGELOG.md`, etc.) — Informative

