### 3.19 Documents Do Not Conform to SOP-DOC-000 Section Template

This is the most pervasive issue. `SOP-DOC-000_Writing_Specification.md` (Section IX) mandates that **all normative documents** (ARC, DOM, FEAT, SOP, SEC-CONT) must follow this exact section order:

```
I.   Purpose          — Single paragraph statement
II.  Scope            — What this document governs
III. Authority Level   — Tier classification and subordination
IV.  Dependencies      — Documents this document derives from
[V+] Content Sections  — Document-specific normative content
[Last] Amendment       — Procedure for revising this document
```

All documents must include a correct **frontmatter table** immediately after the title:
```markdown
| Reference Number | Version | Effective Date | Supersedes | Authority Level |
```

All formal sections must use **Roman numerals** at the top level (I, II, III...) with Arabic numerals (1, 2, 3...) for subsections.

**Informative documents** (LOG-*, SEC-AUD/INC/VUL/THR) do NOT require this normative structure, but MUST still have a correct frontmatter table.

#### Specific Non-Conforming Patterns Observed

| Pattern | Example Files | Problem |
|---|---|---|
| YAML frontmatter instead of the required markdown table | `ARC-OPS-003`, `ARC-OPS-005`, `ARC-OPS-006`, `ARC-OPS-007`, `ARC-OPS-008`, `ARC-OPS-009` | Have `---` YAML blocks with `title:`, `category:`, `roles:` that are not part of the standard |
| Arabic numeral sections instead of Roman | `ARC-OPS-012` uses `1. Purpose`, `2. Core Invariant`; `ARC-OPS-004` uses `1. Core Purpose`, `2. Design Philosophy` | Must be `I. Purpose`, `II. Scope`, etc. |
| Missing required sections entirely | `ARC-OPS-003` has no Purpose, Scope, Authority, Dependencies, or Amendment section | Must add all required sections |
| Informal section names | `ARC-OPS-006` uses `What This Document Covers`, `System Overview`; `ARC-OPS-009` uses `Overview` | Must use the canonical names from SOP-DOC-000 |
| `"Full Documentation"` footer boilerplate | `ARC-OPS-003`, `ARC-OPS-005`, `ARC-OPS-006`, `ARC-OPS-007`, `ARC-OPS-008` all end with a generic GitHub link block | Remove this — it adds no value and is not part of the standard |
| `Last Updated:` date outside frontmatter | `ARC-OPS-006`, `ARC-OPS-009`, `ARC-OPS-013` | The Effective Date in the frontmatter table IS the update date. Remove redundant inline dates |
| `Status: Active` or `Status: Authoritative` inline | `ARC-IDEN-001`, `ARC-OPS-013`, `SOP-DOC-005` | Authority Level in the frontmatter table IS the status indicator. Remove redundant inline status |
| Missing Amendment section | Most ARC-OPS files, `DOM-ECON-001`, `SEC-CORE-000`, `LOG-CORE-000` | Must add Amendment section as the last section |
| Content sections not numbered with Roman numerals | `DOM-ECON-001` uses `## Overview`, `## Components`, `## Troubleshooting` with no numbering | Must be `V. Overview`, `VI. Components`, etc. |

#### Content Rewrite Rule

**Preserve the substance. Reorganize the structure.**

The information within each document must NOT be changed — the facts, rules, code examples, tables, and technical details stay the same. What changes is:

1. **Section ordering** — rearranged to match the SOP-DOC-000 template
2. **Section naming** — renamed to use the canonical names (I. Purpose, II. Scope, etc.)
3. **Section numbering** — converted to Roman numerals at top level
4. **Frontmatter** — corrected or added to match the standard table format
5. **Boilerplate removal** — delete `Full Documentation` footers, redundant `Last Updated:` lines, redundant `Status:` lines, YAML frontmatter blocks
6. **Amendment section** — added if missing
7. **Language register** — normative docs use "must", "shall", "required", "prohibited"; informative docs use "should", "recommended", "typically"

